Program: Last Word
Title: Peter Gibson, AA Gill, Coral Atkins, William Chaloner, Ian McCaskill
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08504ll
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 18 Dec 2016
Matthew Bannister on Peter Gibson the master glazier who devoted his life to the care of the stained glass windows in York Minster. AA Gill, who overcame alcoholism and dyslexia to become one of the UK's best known critics. Coral Atkins who gave up a career as an actress to run homes for disadvantaged children. William Chaloner, an authority on fossil plants who used pollen from the past to reconstruct ancient environments. Ian McCaskill, the BBC weather man much imitated by impressionists. Show less